question.title: The lombok builder cannot generate a complete method
question.body:
I encountered a problem when using lombok on STS. I used the @SuperBuilder annotation in a class, but the generated builder() method was incomplete.

@Data
@SuperBuilder
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor(access = PRIVATE)
public class Recipient extends AuditingBase<String> implements Serializable {

  @Singular
  private List<Commission> commissions = Lists.newArrayList();

  @Default
  BigDecimal commission = ZERO;

}

The commission in the builder() generated here only has the method with Commission as parameter and does not have the option of using BigDecimal as parameter.

This also affects my Mapper. My Mapstruct uses lombok's builder() when generating implementations.

I have currently tried to compile without using an IDE but through cmd. Although it can be run after compilation. But my use of builder() in IDE is still incomplete.

question_comments.body: And,I changed the name of BigDecimal commission It can be compiled normally.
Yes, the result of Maven compilation is different. It can run. Eclipse will report an error when compiling, so no mapstrut implementation will be generated at all.
That doesn't really answer my questions...

The result generated by Eclipse is incomplete, as the commission only has one parameter type, which is of type Commission. When compiling with the Maven command, the application can be started using Spring tools, but the content displayed in the IDE is still incorrect.
Does the javac/maven/gradle compilation yield different results than in Eclipse? If that is the case, that's definitely a bug.

I suspect that this is due to the names of the generated methods clashing: Due to @Singular, the builder's setter method for commissions will have the same name as for commission. Have you tried changing the name for one of the fields?
